<br>
Although, I believe that a fair portion of your back cast loss of power is the same reason that Nolan Ryan doesn't throw a basball backwards have you considered the &quot;power snap&quot; that Bill was talking about. Are you directing some portion of the loops energy &quot;down&quot; in your back cast in lieu of at your target. You are &quot;much&quot; more likely to do this in the back cast than you are in the forward cast since the wrist can bend so much easier in the back than it can in the front.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=andrewcolley@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Andrew Colley</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Little Red River Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#000000>(10/13/03 12:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with the old backcast</span><hr size=1> Hey Chuck,<br>
